{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489585","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489585"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:22:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:22:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"696"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"696","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/696"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.15,0.72,0.05,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"696"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59547"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"696","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/696"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"696"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44956"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"2349"},{"type":"tags","id":"4139"},{"type":"tags","id":"4687"},{"type":"tags","id":"4689"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"6344"},{"type":"tags","id":"6496"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2743"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2800"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43033"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44624"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59547","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/59547"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 46-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a seven-month history of urinary urgency and incontinence. She reports a strong, frequent urge to urinate and occasionally leaks urine before reaching the bathroom. Episodes occur both day and night. She has previously tried pelvic floor exercises, bladder training and reducing caffeine intake without improvement. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. Her obstetric history includes three caesarean sections. Her menstrual cycles are regular.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well. Her pulse rate is 82/min, blood pressure 136/89 mmHg and temperature 37.1\u00b0C. There is no urine leakage on coughing. Urinalysis is normal and post-void residual volume is 40 mL.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Intravaginal oestrogen","Vaginal pessary","Oral oxybutynin","Tension-free vaginal tape","Oral bethanechol"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with urge incontinence, characterised by sudden urge to void with or without urinary leakage. The normal post-void residual volume and absence of stress incontinence on examination suggest detrusor overactivity as the underlying cause.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral oxybutynin\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate next step as the patient has failed conservative management. Anticholinergic medications reduce detrusor muscle overactivity by blocking parasympathetic stimulation. Common side effects include dry mouth, constipation, and blurred vision.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravaginal oestrogen\u003C/strong\u003E is used for urogenital atrophy in postmenopausal women. This patient has regular menstrual cycles and no symptoms of vaginal atrophy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVaginal pessary\u003C/strong\u003E is used for stress urinary incontinence or pelvic organ prolapse. This patient has no evidence of stress incontinence on examination (no leakage with coughing).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETension-free vaginal tape\u003C/strong\u003E is a surgical treatment for stress urinary incontinence. It would not help with symptoms of urge incontinence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral bethanechol\u003C/strong\u003E is a cholinergic medication used for urinary retention or overflow incontinence with elevated post-void residual volumes. This patient\u0027s post-void residual volume is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Urge incontinence is characterised by sudden urge to void with or without urinary leakage, often due to detrusor overactivity","First-line management of urge incontinence includes lifestyle changes, bladder training and pelvic floor exercises","Anticholinergic medications are indicated for urge incontinence when conservative measures fail"],"references":["McDonnell B, Birder LA. Recent advances in pharmacological management of urinary incontinence. F1000Res. 2017;6:2148. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5749129/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44956"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"696"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44956","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/44956"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-08T12:52:34+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-08T12:54:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"696"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59547"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3